answers.body_markdown:
The `Aggregate` method in the Go driver accepts a `pipeline` parameter, which should be a slice of documents, each representing a pipeline stage. `$lookup` would be one of these stages. For example, the pipeline
`[{$lookup: {from: &quot;foo&quot;, as:&quot;bar&quot;}}]` would be written in the Go driver as:

    coll.Aggregate(ctx, mongo.Pipeline{
        {{&quot;$lookup&quot;, bson.D{{&quot;from&quot;, &quot;foo&quot;}, {&quot;as&quot;, &quot;bar&quot;}}}},
    })

