There is no way to make `collate` work with any regex `find` logic, since the regex script will override any `collate` definition, and only use the logic defined within itself, namely find any string that contains half-width `` only. 

The simplest way to achieve this is to add an extra logic before you send the search text into your MongoDB client, and duplicate the text into both half &amp; full width. You can use some existing tool like [this](https://mariten.github.io/kanatools-java/en/kana-converter/).

Then apply both half &amp; full width search parameters into your `find` condition with `$or`;

    db.mycollection.find({$or: [{&quot;desc&quot;://}, {&quot;desc&quot;://}]}) 

Same issue;

 - [Use of collation in mongodb $regex
](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41441071/use-of-collation-in-mongodb-regex)

